Introduction
Digital literacy is an essential skill in today’s technology-driven world. As a Student Digital Ambassador, this project helped me understand how to effectively use digital tools, maintain a professional online presence, and ensure safe and responsible behavior online. The project consisted of five tasks, each focusing on a different aspect of digital literacy such as awareness, portfolio building, coding platforms, communication, and cybersecurity. Through this project, I explored various tools like GitHub, LinkedIn, Google Forms, and HackerRank. I also learned how to communicate professionally through emails and how to protect myself from cyber threats. Overall, this project has enhanced my understanding of the digital world and prepared me to guide others as well.

Task 1
For this task, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The infographic was designed to help students understand the importance of digital literacy in a simple and visually appealing way. I included key topics such as the definition of digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, and safe internet practices. The design consisted of icons, headings, and short bullet points to make the content easy to understand.
I explained that digital literacy involves the ability to use digital tools effectively and responsibly. I also included tools like Google Docs, GitHub, and LinkedIn, which are helpful for academic and professional growth. Additionally, I added safety tips such as not sharing personal information and avoiding suspicious links.
One challenge I faced was organizing all the information in a single page without making it look cluttered. However, this helped me improve my design and presentation skills. Overall, this task was interesting and improved my creativity.

Task 2
In this task, I created my digital portfolio by setting up profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Stack Overflow. Each platform serves a different purpose and helps in building a professional online presence.
GitHub is used for showcasing projects and coding work. I created a profile README where I added my name, branch, and a short introduction. LinkedIn is a professional networking platform where I added my education details and created a basic profile. Stack Overflow is a community-based platform where developers ask and answer programming-related questions, helping users learn from real-world problems.
These platforms are important because they help students build their identity in the digital world. Over the next four years, I plan to use GitHub to upload my projects, LinkedIn to connect with professionals and explore opportunities, and Stack Overflow to learn from discussions and improve my problem-solving skills.
This task helped me understand the importance of maintaining a professional online presence from the beginning of my career.

Task 3 

For this task, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I created an account on HackerRank and completed a beginner-level problem called "Solve Me First." This helped me understand basic problem-solving and how coding platforms work.
In the second part, I created a Google Form consisting of five questions related to digital literacy awareness. The form included multiple-choice and short-answer questions.
also viewed the responses in Google Sheets, which showed how data is collected and analyzed.
These tools are very useful for students. HackerRank helps in improving coding skills and preparing for technical interviews. Google Forms is useful for conducting surveys, quizzes, and collecting feedback.
This task helped me understand how digital tools can be used for both learning and collaboration. It also improved my confidence in using online platforms effectively.

Task 4

Poor digital communication can create misunderstandings and affect professional relationships. For example, sending an email without a proper subject line or using informal language with a professor can create a negative impression. In some cases, unclear communication can lead to missed deadlines or confusion.
To avoid such issues, it is important to follow proper email etiquette. This includes using a clear subject line, polite language, and a structured format. One should always review the email before sending it.
This task helped me understand the importance of professional communication and how small mistakes can have a big impact. I learned how to write clear and respectful emails in a formal environment.

Task 5 
While researching cybercrime, I was surprised to learn how common and easy UPI frauds have become. Many people fall victim to scams due to lack of awareness.
Fraudsters use simple tricks like fake payment requests or phishing links to steal money.
This made me realize the importance of being cautious while using online payment systems. One habit I will change is verifying every payment request before accepting it and never sharing OTPs with anyone.
This task helped me understand the risks involved in the digital world and how important it is to stay alert and informed.


Conclusion
This project helped me gain practical knowledge about digital literacy and its importance in daily life. I learned how to use various digital platforms, communicate professionally, and stay safe online. Each task provided valuable insights into different aspects of the digital world. The experience also improved my confidence in using online tools and building a professional identity. Overall, this project was very informative and useful for my academic and personal growth.
